{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how verifiability of child-story closure condition will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fd5106e237164830e"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"verifiability of child-story closure condition"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for file-ownership boundary between sibling stories — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f82524518cbf636a6","fa5152e8606306dbe"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"file-ownership boundary between sibling stories"},{"coaching":"Pin down identity-core call chain channel attribution with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["ffa5f5431c594d260"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"identity-core call chain channel attribution"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for inferred-marker formal schema encoding — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f90d2b2397af1c9b1"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"inferred-marker formal schema encoding"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on downstream consumer break on code revert: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fdbd5ed50001207b6"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"downstream consumer break on code revert"},{"coaching":"Plan how export NDJSON creation-channel verification ownership will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f8ea9f273233d57e1"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"export NDJSON creation-channel verification ownership"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for import-semantics documentation placement contract — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f305f5392487d3c7f"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"import-semantics documentation placement contract"},{"coaching":"Pin down acceptance-criteria completeness and testability with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"acceptance-criteria completeness and testability"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":9,"blocking":0,"dropped":8,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":8034,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":2,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"fail"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2025,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":3387},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":292.9,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":552627.2,"total_ms":553034.4,"verify_requests":17},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":false,"registry_unchanged":false,"sidecar_baseline":false,"within_window":false}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either prefix the 'three child stories are closed' sub-criterion with `[operator-attested]` (per ADR 0043) so it is met by a recorded attestation, or replace it with a fully in-session-verifiable formulation (e.g., each child story's change is present in `git log` and the depends_on graph is satisfied).","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The three child stories are closed' — ticket closure is a project-management state outside the repository","The two proof commands (`rebar deps` and `git log`) verify hierarchy and code presence but neither returns ticket closure status","The criterion does not carry the [operator-attested] prefix specified by ADR 0043"],"finding":"AC5 includes 'the three child stories are closed' as a required condition, but this is a project-management state that is not verifiable in-session by the stated commands (`uv run rebar deps jira-reb-977` checks hierarchy, not closure status; `git log` checks code presence), and the criterion is not tagged [operator-attested] to signal that external attestation is acceptable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd5106e237164830e","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC5: 'The three child stories are closed and their reviewed changes are present in the feature branch merged to main'","norm_id":"n8fbac3e2210b6741","priority":0.44,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor who has merged all code but whose ticketing system auto-close is delayed cannot deterministically pass this criterion in-session","A reviewer cannot verify 'closed' status from the repository alone"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Change the opening of AC5 to: '[operator-attested] The three child stories are closed and their reviewed changes are present in the feature branch merged to main; prove code presence with `uv run rebar deps jira-reb-977` and `git log --oneline --decorate origin/main`.`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/event-schema.md: 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 & 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 (no ordering edge)","src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 & 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 (no ordering edge)"],"finding":"Sibling tickets touch the same file(s) with no ordering edge.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f82524518cbf636a6","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"na0177dc3af65d74f","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a depends_on/blocks edge to serialize, or partition the file ownership.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["6 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how `creation_channel='jira'` reaches `ensure_identity_for` → `create_identity_core` → `create_core` when the reconciler mints a placeholder identity via `_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity`; update the file-impact list in Story 2 (e622) to name the required signature changes on `create_identity_core` and `ensure_identity_for`, and add a test case for reconciler-path placeholder identity attribution.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Story 2 states: 'Reconciler-created placeholder identities produced as part of inbound materialization also receive jira explicitly'","apply_inbound_records.py:_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity calls rebar.ensure_identity_for() with no channel argument (line 69)","identity.py:ensure_identity_for() calls create_identity_core() (line 373) with no channel arg","identity.py:create_identity_core() calls create_core() (line 291) with no channel arg","Story 1 specifies create_core gains a required keyword-only creation_channel parameter","File impact for Story 2 lists _commands/identity.py but does not describe the ensure_identity_for parameter threading requirement"],"finding":"The ensure_identity_for → create_identity_core → create_core call chain, used best-effort by the Jira reconciler's _ensure_inbound_assignee_identity, is not traced as a path that needs explicit channel threading. The plan states reconciler-created placeholder identities 'receive jira explicitly', but ensure_identity_for() has no creation_channel parameter, and if create_core gains a required creation_channel kwarg (as Story 1 specifies), this entire chain must be updated with a jira channel or a suitable default — yet the plan names no mechanism for this.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffa5f5431c594d260","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions / Scope IN — 'All CREATE-backed helper flows'; Story e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What section: 'Reconciler-created placeholder identities produced as part of inbound materialization also receive jira explicitly'; apply_inbound_records.py:_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity → rebar.ensure_identity_for → identity.create_identity_core → create_core","norm_id":"n9359d25f753991cd","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Story 1 makes creation_channel a required keyword-only arg on create_core; ensure_identity_for/create_identity_core are not updated → TypeError at runtime when the reconciler calls rebar.ensure_identity_for() during an inbound Jira create.","Story 1 gives create_core a default creation_channel='python' fallback to avoid breaking callers; placeholder identities minted by the Jira reconciler would then silently report python instead of jira."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add an optional `creation_channel` parameter (defaulting to `'python'` for non-reconciler callers) to both `create_identity_core` and `ensure_identity_for`, and have the reconciler's `_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity` pass `creation_channel='jira'`. This mirrors how source_* provenance is already threaded through `create_core` via the `identity` dict.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In the story 6fe2 schema definition for `creation_channel_inferred`, specify the formal JSON Schema constraint (e.g., `\"const\": true`) that enforces 'present only when true', and note this in the Architecture Decisions section so the schema encoding is co-located with the decision rule.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'The inference marker is present only when true. It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.'","ticket_state.schema.json uses 'additionalProperties: true' — any value for creation_channel_inferred passes schema validation until the field is explicitly defined","Story 6fe2 specifies adding 'optional public schema fields creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred to ticket_state.schema.json' but does not state the formal schema constraint (e.g., const: true) that encodes the 'present only when true' rule","ABSENCE: no schema snippet or formal encoding of the 'const: true / absent-when-false' rule appears anywhere in the plan or child stories"],"finding":"The `creation_channel_inferred: true` 'present only when true' constraint is stated only in plan prose; no formal schema encoding is specified, leaving it possible for a conformant schema implementation to store `false` and pass validation since ticket_state.schema.json uses `additionalProperties: true`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f90d2b2397af1c9b1","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The inference marker is present only when true. It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.'; child story 6fe2 What section — 'The marker accepts only boolean true and is absent for recorded/unknown values.'","norm_id":"n2b6b4d694d7f2afa","priority":0.2063,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A reducer implementation stores creation_channel_inferred: false for non-inferred tickets; schema validation passes but consumers treating the marker as present-only get incorrect results","A future schema generator round-trip emits the field as nullable boolean rather than const: true, silently breaking the diagnostic contract"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In ticket_state.schema.json, define: `\"creation_channel_inferred\": { \"const\": true, \"description\": \"Present only when the channel was inferred from historical signals; absent for recorded and unknown values.\" }`. Reference this encoding in the Architecture Decisions section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit note in e622 (or 6fe2) describing the boundary within identity.py: 6fe2 owns the public create_identity API attribution; e622 owns the internal reconciler placeholder path, and specify the shared internal interface (e.g., a channel parameter) that e622 will call.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["6fe2 file_impact: {\"path\": \"src/rebar/_commands/identity.py\", \"reason\": \"identity creation attribution\"}","e622 file_impact: {\"path\": \"src/rebar/_commands/identity.py\", \"reason\": \"attribute reconciler-created placeholder identities\"}","No plan text in either child delineates which specific function or call site each child modifies within identity.py","e622 depends_on 6fe2, so merge ordering is enforced, but the interface contract between the two edits is implicit","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"src/rebar/_commands/identity.py appears in the file_impact of both 6fe2 (public-API identity attribution) and e622 (reconciler placeholder identity attribution) without explicit coordination language about which functions each child modifies, creating an unacknowledged scope overlap in a shared file.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa5152e8606306dbe","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 file_impact (identity.py: 'identity creation attribution'); child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 file_impact (identity.py: 'attribute reconciler-created placeholder identities')","norm_id":"n0d7cec36415c394b","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["6fe2 refactors identity.py's create_identity function signature to accept a creation_channel parameter; e622 assumes a different call site or helper structure for reconciler placeholder identities, producing a merge conflict or silent double-attribution on the feature branch."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In e622's description or scope, add: 'identity.py changes extend the reconciler-internal call path introduced by 6fe2; the public create_identity API channel parameter added by 6fe2 is reused with channel=jira for placeholder creation.' This makes the dependency surface explicit.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend the back-out/rollback section to explicitly address the output-schema consumer impact: either add an expand-contract note (new field remains present but empty/unknown on rollback) or document that consumers must be notified before reverting, so the rollback remedy covers both event-log and public-output dimensions.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Back-out is code-only: reverting the readers/writers leaves event logs valid because unknown event-data keys are already forward-compatible.\"","The plan does not mention what happens to consumers of the public output schema (show/list/export, typed surfaces) that have already adopted the new field when code is reverted.","ABSENCE: no expand-contract sequence or consumer communication step is described for the output-schema side of rollback."],"finding":"The rollback/back-out description covers event-log safety (additive keys, code revert) but does not address the consumer-facing break: downstream consumers that have begun reading `creation_channel` from public show/list/export outputs or typed schemas would lose the field if code is reverted, which is a silent regression not acknowledged in the plan.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdbd5ed50001207b6","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Back-out is code-only' paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — Compatibility bullet","norm_id":"n21c13854e8ce3d99","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A downstream script or integration reads `creation_channel` from exported NDJSON or the ticket_state schema; the field disappears after a rollback; the consumer breaks silently.","An auditor workflow is built on `creation_channel_inferred`; rollback removes it from outputs without warning."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence to the Compatibility risk bullet: 'On rollback, consumers reading creation_channel from show/list/export outputs will lose the field; coordinate consumer notification or keep the output key present (returning unknown) before retiring the writer code.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Assign ownership of tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py (verifying creation_channel appears in exported NDJSON records) to one child — most naturally e622, which owns import/export semantics.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC3: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py'","6fe2 file_impact and ACs: no mention of test_export_ndjson.py; 6fe2 scope OUT includes 'NDJSON import'","e622 file_impact and ACs: test_creation_channel.py (io) covers import-side but test_export_ndjson.py is absent; e622 scope is 'import/export semantics' but the specific export NDJSON test file is not claimed","568c file_impact and ACs: no mention of test_export_ndjson.py","G4 consumer-impact worklist: NDJSON export is a consumer of TicketState schema and must propagate creation_channel through the export serialization path; no child owns verification of this path","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC3's proof suite includes tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py, but no child lists this file in its ACs, file_impact, or verify_commands — the export NDJSON serialization path for creation_channel is owned by none.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8ea9f273233d57e1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent AC3 (proof command: uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py); all three children","norm_id":"n0d0f5da9b2ad8bf2","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["test_export_ndjson.py is run as part of parent AC3 verification and fails because no child added creation_channel to the NDJSON export serialization; the parent epic cannot be closed.","NDJSON export silently drops creation_channel — auditors who export and re-import lose provenance — without this test catching the regression."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py to e622's file_impact and include it in e622's AC that covers export behavior (e.g., extend the import AC or add a new AC: 'NDJSON export includes creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred in serialized records. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py').","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Assign documentation of import semantics in docs/output-schemas.md to one child (e622 is the natural owner); add docs/output-schemas.md to e622's file_impact with a note covering the import/source_* distinction.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC6: 'Documentation in docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md defines the CREATE/SNAPSHOT placement, enum, inference predicate, import semantics, and distinction from actor/environment/source_* provenance.'","e622 Files: 'docs/event-schema.md and docs/cli-reference.md: Jira/import semantics' — output-schemas.md not listed","6fe2 Files: 'docs/output-schemas.md: public output semantics' — but 6fe2 scope OUT explicitly excludes import, so import semantics will not be written to output-schemas.md by 6fe2","568c Files: docs/event-schema.md and docs/concurrency.md — output-schemas.md not listed for import content","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC6 requires docs/output-schemas.md to define 'import semantics', but the only child that documents import (e622) assigns that documentation to docs/event-schema.md and docs/cli-reference.md — leaving import semantics in docs/output-schemas.md unassigned.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f305f5392487d3c7f","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent AC6; child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 Scope and Files sections; child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 Files section","norm_id":"n6208015af8be86c7","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["docs/output-schemas.md is updated by 6fe2 with local channel vocabulary but never receives the import semantics section; parent AC6 test_schema_coverage.py passes for enum but fails for import semantics completeness.","Auditors reading output-schemas.md to understand import behavior find no guidance, defeating the parent's documentation goal."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In e622, add docs/output-schemas.md to the Files list with the note 'import channel semantics and distinction from source_* provenance' to mirror the event-schema.md entry.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the exact string literal(s) that identify a reconciler author and env_id in the Architecture Decisions inference predicate (e.g., `author == 'jira-reconciler'` and `env_id == 'jira-reconciler'`), so the implementor and test author share the same boundary.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler' — the string value of 'reconciler' for author and env_id is not stated","The plan cites apply_inbound_records.py as the creation seam but does not quote the literal author/env_id values the reconciler writes"],"finding":"The historical inference predicate requires that 'genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler' but never states what string literal(s) constitute a 'reconciler' identity for those fields. An executor must discover these values from the codebase, which is not guaranteed to be unambiguous.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3098b7bcca782a40","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Those projections also carry creation_channel_inferred: true. Every other historical record projects unknown'","norm_id":"n43edfcebdc33e2eb","priority":0.033,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementor uncertain whether to match 'reconciler', 'jira-reconciler', a UUID, or a sentinel string writes a predicate that silently under- or over-matches historical records","Near-miss negative test cases (required by the Risks section) cannot be written without knowing the exact boundary value"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence such as: 'The reconciler author is the literal string `jira-reconciler` and the reconciler env_id is the literal string `jira-reconciler`; these are the exact values written by apply_inbound_records.py and are the required match values for the inference predicate.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a sub-bullet to Architecture Decisions specifying the exact fallback for legacy-SNAPSHOT-only replay (e.g., 'apply the same historical Jira inference predicate to compiled_state signals; otherwise project unknown') so AC4's legacy-SNAPSHOT scenario has a concrete, testable definition.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["COH","E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC4: 'Full-log, compacted SNAPSHOT-only, legacy-SNAPSHOT, and rebuilt-SNAPSHOT replay produce identical recorded/inferred/unknown provenance after folded CREATE events are retired.'","Architecture Decisions compaction bullet: 'SNAPSHOT-only replay and snapshot rebuild must reproduce the same creation provenance as full-log replay.' — this only describes new SNAPSHOTs, not pre-feature SNAPSHOTs.","ABSENCE: No section of the plan describes what logic runs when compiled_state is missing creation_channel (i.e., a snapshot written before this feature)."],"finding":"AC4 mandates that 'legacy-SNAPSHOT replay' produces correct provenance, but the Architecture Decisions section never specifies the fallback behavior when a pre-feature SNAPSHOT (whose compiled_state lacks creation_channel) is the sole replay source — the plan is silent on whether the reducer applies historical inference, returns unknown, or errors.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3f06441a1288e039","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC4 ('legacy-SNAPSHOT' scenario) vs Architecture Decisions ('Compaction preserves creation_channel...' bullet)","norm_id":"n3c01f03b663495d3","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer writing the legacy-SNAPSHOT replay path has no spec to follow — they must guess whether to apply the Jira inference predicate, return unknown, or propagate a default.","The AC4 test can only be written correctly if the expected output for a legacy SNAPSHOT is defined; without a spec the test may encode the wrong expectation."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In Architecture Decisions, extend the compaction bullet: 'When a SNAPSHOT written before this feature is the only replay source, the reducer reads compiled_state signals and applies the same three-signal Jira predicate; all other legacy SNAPSHOTs project unknown. This mirrors full-log historical inference and ensures AC4 legacy-SNAPSHOT expectations are deterministic.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"insufficient","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a `docs/decisions/` ADR (or equivalent in-repo decision record) for the creation-channel vocabulary, Jira inference predicate, and diagnostic-not-security trust boundary, and reference it from the documentation AC.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added. A future ingress such as a GitHub reconciler extends the closed vocabulary deliberately.\" — this is a binding constraint with future implications that benefits from a durable ADR.","\"The inference marker is present only when true. It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.\" — trust-boundary ruling that should be findable by future authors.","ABSENCE: no `docs/decisions/NNNN-creation-channel.md` or equivalent ADR file is specified in Scope IN or AC."],"finding":"The plan introduces a non-trivial architectural decision — a closed immutable enum for creation channel, a three-signal Jira inference predicate, and rules distinguishing diagnostic trust from security attestation — but specifies no durable ADR document; the inline Architecture Decisions section is not a persisted decision record and may not be discoverable alongside future architectural changes.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fea07cc61fde67c36","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section; Success Criteria — documentation bullet","norm_id":"nc3174c2edb0378f9","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future engineer adding a GitHub reconciler cannot find the rationale for the closed vocabulary or the exact Jira inference predicate rules and either reopens the design debate or makes an inconsistent extension.","A security review asks why creation_channel is not attested; the only record is in this plan document, not in the repo."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR (or equivalent CLAUDE.md section) capturing the closed-vocabulary governance policy, the Jira-only inference predicate rationale, the trust-boundary distinction for `creation_channel_inferred`, and the additive/no-migration contract — and reference it from the existing doc AC.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan's 'Architecture Decisions' section contains rich rationale but is embedded in the ticket, not a versioned design artifact","AC for documentation references only 'docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md' — no ADR or CLAUDE.md update is required","'The inference marker is present only when true. It is diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation.' — this trust-boundary distinction is a key design decision that should survive beyond the ticket lifetime","'No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added. A future ingress such as a GitHub reconciler extends the closed vocabulary deliberately.' — vocabulary governance policy not captured in a durable location"],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel architectural decision (an immutable audit dimension with a closed vocabulary, conservative Jira-only historical inference semantics, and a trust-boundary distinction for the inference marker) but does not explicitly require an ADR or CLAUDE.md update to capture the design rationale durably alongside the code.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f78806dd1f9558912","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section; Success Criteria / AC for documentation","norm_id":"n8c1451c839c88067","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future contributor adds a new ingress without knowing the closed-vocabulary governance policy and introduces a free-form string, breaking schema validation","Inference semantics (three-signal predicate, jira-only, false-positive controls) are re-litigated in code review because the rationale is not in a discoverable design doc","A SNAPSHOT-only replay regression is debugged without knowing the architectural invariant that SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state must preserve creation_channel_inferred"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md summarizing: (1) why a closed enum rather than free-form, (2) why inference is limited to Jira with three required signals, (3) the diagnostic-not-security-attestation trust boundary for the inference marker, (4) the additive contract and forward-compatibility guarantee. Add a line to the documentation AC: 'An ADR is present at docs/adr/ and referenced from docs/event-schema.md.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend the rollback description to assert the observable schema state after a code rollback for tickets already compacted with `creation_channel` in `compiled_state` — either confirm that the old `process_snapshot` generic restore silently carries the field (no DATA LOSS, but invisible to old output schemas) or add a compensating-forward note clarifying whether this is acceptable.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Back-out is code-only: reverting the readers/writers leaves event logs valid because unknown event-data keys are already forward-compatible.'","ABSENCE: no assertion about the projected/observable schema state for already-compacted tickets after a code rollback.","process_snapshot restores all compiled_state keys verbatim ('for key, value in compiled_state.items(): state[key] = value' in src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:747-748), so post-compaction SNAPSHOTs carrying creation_channel will silently populate that field in internal state even under a rolled-back reader.","T11 rubric: 'the plan must assert on the schema STATE AFTER rollback, not merely that rollback exits 0'"],"finding":"The rollback description ('Back-out is code-only: reverting the readers/writers leaves event logs valid') addresses raw-bytes forward-compatibility but does not assert the observable projected state after rollback for tickets already compacted under the new code — SNAPSHOTs with creation_channel baked into compiled_state will have those keys silently present in internal reducer state after rollback (restored verbatim by process_snapshot's generic key loop) but invisible to rolled-back output schemas, and no DATA LOSS RISK note clarifies whether this silent retention is intentional.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a1d68bb78ea9886","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The public change is additive. Older readers ignore the new CREATE keys… Back-out is code-only'","norm_id":"n8f1a87f6a925c4f5","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Compaction runs under new code, writing creation_channel=cli into a SNAPSHOT's compiled_state. Code is rolled back. The old reader's output schema has no creation_channel field, but internal state has it. Auditors relying on the channel for compliance observe a gap (field present in store, absent in outputs) with no documented explanation.","A monitoring script checking for absence of creation_channel in outputs incorrectly concludes no tickets have been attributed, when in fact they are attributed in stored state."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In Architecture Decisions (and story e622 What section), state the exact literal string(s) used as the comparison target for the `author` and `env_id` inference signals (e.g., `\"reconciler\"` per `_event_meta()` defaults) and specify whether env-overridden reconciler identities are in or out of scope.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states: 'the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler. Those projections also carry creation_channel_inferred: true'","Story e622 states: 'author equals reconciler, and env_id equals reconciler. All comparisons are exact.'","Code evidence: src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py:166-167 shows _event_meta() returns _rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler') and _rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler') — the literal default is 'reconciler', but this is env-overridable and nowhere stated in the plan","ABSENCE: the plan never writes the string literal 'reconciler' as the comparison target, leaving the predicate ambiguous for any deployment that overrides REBAR_AUTHOR or REBAR_ENV_ID"],"finding":"The historical inference predicate requires exact string comparison for 'reconciler' author and env_id, but the plan never specifies the literal string value(s) that constitute a 'reconciler' identity for this comparison — an implementer reading only the plan cannot write a correct predicate.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f801762d68f8611e3","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section — 'genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler'; child story e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What section — 'author equals reconciler, and env_id equals reconciler'","norm_id":"ne2c43e21ef5e162b","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer writes the predicate comparing against a config value or env variable rather than the hardcoded string 'reconciler', causing inference to fail or fire incorrectly","A future deployment that sets REBAR_AUTHOR=jira-bot produces legacy tickets where author != 'reconciler', but the plan's 'exact' rule provides no guidance on whether non-default reconciler authors are in scope"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Architecture Decisions: 'The inference predicate compares author == \"reconciler\" and env_id == \"reconciler\" — the exact default strings produced by _event_meta() in inbound_translate.py. Deployments that override REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID for the reconciler process will not match historical records written with non-default values; those records project unknown.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In the Architecture Decisions inference rule and story 568c, explicitly specify the fallback behavior when `author` or `env_id` is absent or None in a legacy SNAPSHOT's `compiled_state` (e.g., 'any absent/None signal counts as a predicate mismatch and projects unknown').","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["process_snapshot (src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:744-791) restores compiled_state verbatim; pre-feature compiled_state carries author/env_id from process_create, but it is not guaranteed","The plan states 'All comparisons are exact' for the three-signal predicate but does not specify what happens when author or env_id is None/absent in compiled_state","Story 568c specifies 'A pre-feature SNAPSHOT lacking both keys projects inferred Jira only for the exact three-signal predicate' — but a pre-feature SNAPSHOT may also lack author/env_id in compiled_state if the CREATE was malformed or the snapshot was compacted from partial state","ABSENCE: no fallback behavior is specified for missing author/env_id fields in the SNAPSHOT compiled_state inference path"],"finding":"The legacy SNAPSHOT inference path (story 568c) reads `author` and `env_id` from restored `compiled_state`, but pre-feature SNAPSHOTs may not contain these fields — the plan specifies no fallback for the case where a legacy SNAPSHOT's `compiled_state` lacks `author` or `env_id` entirely.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc81593afb0fecee4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree: the ticket ID uses the reconciler-generated jira- prefix and the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler.'; child story 568c What section — 'After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, run the same legacy projection helper used after CREATE only when creation_channel is absent.'","norm_id":"nf022d510d36c84a7","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A pre-feature SNAPSHOT's compiled_state has author=None (e.g., compacted from a CREATE with no author field); the predicate comparison None == 'reconciler' is False, so it projects unknown — but this case is not explicitly specified, leaving the implementer to infer the behavior","A legacy SNAPSHOT missing env_id causes a KeyError rather than a clean 'unknown' fallback if the helper doesn't defensively handle None"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to Architecture Decisions: 'If any of the three inference signals is absent or None in the compiled_state, the predicate fails and the record projects unknown. A None author or env_id is not equal to \"reconciler\".'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add 'make lint' to at least one child's verify_commands (6fe2 as the documentation foundation child is the natural owner) so it is gated per story rather than only at epic close.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC6: 'Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py and make lint'","6fe2 verify_commands: DD-L1, DD-L2, DD-L3 — none include make lint","e622 verify_commands: DD-X1, DD-X2, DD-X3 — none include make lint","568c verify_commands: DD-S1, DD-S2, DD-S3 — none include make lint","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC6's proof command includes 'make lint', but no child's acceptance criteria or verify_commands references make lint — it is unowned as a per-story deliverable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb0b11888691643a9","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent AC6 (proof: 'make lint'); all three children's ACs and verify_commands","norm_id":"ncf81fc0affd6378c","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Documentation edits across children introduce lint failures (e.g., broken links, schema reference errors); no child's CI gate runs make lint to catch them, deferring the failure to the parent epic's final verification."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In 6fe2, add a verify_command entry: {\"command\": \"make lint\", \"dd_id\": \"DD-L4\", \"dd_text\": \"Documentation linting passes for all new event-schema.md and output-schemas.md additions\"}.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent